response: {"Q0":"The blue deck of cards continues the story with a series of events that is consistent and connected with the opening part of the story. The blue deck continues the story from one part to the next in a way that makes sense and follows a typical story plotline. The red deck continues the story with an unconnected, inconsistent series of events after the first part of the story. The red deck continues the story in a way that doesn't make much sense, and brings up irrelevant things that aren't connected to the story \"plotline\", and often diverges from the initial part of the story to tell you about something else that has happened in the area or in the room that this story is occurring."}
